Here will be all the commands and instructions of tmux that I learn

->: then. for example:
	Ctrl + b -> c means Ctrl and b at the same time, then I press 


Ctrl + b: Start the command mode

With the command mode:
	# Sessions (tabs)
	-> c = Create a new session
	-> , = Change name to a session
	-> w = List all sessions

	# Splits
	-> " = Create a new horizontal split
	-> % = Create a new vertical split
	-> x = Kill the select split
	-> h, j, k, l = navigate in the splits
	->Ctrl + o = rotate splits
